      <h2 class="font-sora text-3xl font-bold text-[#162433] mb-6">Understanding RV Insurance</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-[#4B5563]">
        <p class="mb-4">RV insurance protects your investment against accidents, theft, weather damage, and liability claims. Unlike auto insurance, RV policies must account for your vehicle's dual nature as both transportation and living space.</p>
        <p class="mb-4">The type of RV dramatically affects your insurance needs. A $400,000 Class A diesel pusher needs different coverage than a $15,000 travel trailer. And if you're living in your RV full-time, you need coverage that treats it as your home.</p>
        <p>Don't assume your auto insurance covers your RV. It doesn't—not adequately, anyway. RVs need specialized policies that understand the unique risks involved.</p>
      </div>
